ğŸ¤” What is State in React?

In simple words, state is used to store data that can change over time.
When the state changes, React automatically updates the UI.
This is what makes React fast and dynamic.

Example:

Button click count

User input text

Toggle (ON / OFF)
All these need state.

ğŸ§  Why State is Important?

Before state, I was thinking:

â€œHow does React know when data changes?â€

Now I understand:
ğŸ‘‰ State tells React when to re-render the component.

Without state:

No interaction

No dynamic UI

Just static pages ğŸ˜´

ğŸ› ï¸ Small Example
import { useState } from "react";

function Counter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <>
      <p>Count: {count}</p>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>
        Increase
      </button>
    </>
  );
}


This example helped me understand:

count â†’ current state value

setCount â†’ function to update state

useState(0) â†’ initial value

